WEBVTT

00:06.201 --> 00:07.370
Janko: This blows.

00:07.931 --> 00:09.706
Yeah, boss said it's
just for a few days.

00:09.708 --> 00:12.442
Movie and TV Unit's got more
work than it can handle.

00:12.444 --> 00:14.871
<i>Dempsey and Kane?</i> I never heard of it.

00:14.891 --> 00:16.846
It's a cop show.

00:16.848 --> 00:19.488
Two female detectives.
The acting's not bad, actually,

00:19.508 --> 00:21.841
but the writing is a joke.

00:23.477 --> 00:24.978
Hey.

00:27.327 --> 00:29.249
Man: All right, so, when these
guys come through the arch,

00:29.251 --> 00:30.683
you're gonna take them at gunpoint...

00:30.685 --> 00:32.435
(clears throat) right...

00:33.087 --> 00:34.286
there.

00:35.593 --> 00:37.003
That's money.

00:37.523 --> 00:38.558
Can we mark this, Joe?

00:38.560 --> 00:40.226
Yeah. It's all yours. Thanks, guys.

00:41.028 --> 00:42.128
Hey.

00:42.130 --> 00:44.230
Can you believe they pay me for this?

00:44.232 --> 00:46.466
Joe Pelligrino,
police technical advisor.

00:46.468 --> 00:48.268
Jamie Reagan. This is my
partner, Eddie Janko.

00:48.270 --> 00:50.336
So, you help the actors

00:50.338 --> 00:51.938
- act like cops?
- Mm-hmm.

00:51.940 --> 00:52.939
Today's audience
is pretty sophisticated,

00:52.941 --> 00:54.140
so we got to get it right.

00:54.142 --> 00:55.942
- Sounds like a pretty good gig.
- Yeah,

00:55.944 --> 00:58.152
but I'd kill to be back
on the job... nothing like that.

00:58.172 --> 00:59.504
Well, hey, what'd you guys
think of the scene?

00:59.524 --> 01:01.931
Pretty good, but the two
detectives were at 12 and six

01:01.951 --> 01:04.186
- when they cornered the perp.
- That's crossfire.

01:04.206 --> 01:05.111
It's kind of dangerous.

01:05.113 --> 01:06.279
Well, that, uh, blocking,

01:06.281 --> 01:08.381
it saves us two setups,
and time is money.

01:08.383 --> 01:10.616
Also, I don't think that
I'd work the street

01:10.618 --> 01:13.227
in heels or a skirt that tight.

01:13.247 --> 01:14.220
Pelligrino: That's a network note.

01:14.222 --> 01:15.554
Those guys write the checks, so...

01:15.556 --> 01:17.156
It's just not very realistic.

01:17.158 --> 01:18.824
Yeah, well, you know,
we got a saying on set:

01:18.826 --> 01:20.126
"We're not making a documentary here."

01:20.128 --> 01:21.827
(chuckles) All right.
Hey, you guys check out

01:21.829 --> 01:24.089
the chicken tacos over at craft service.

01:24.109 --> 01:25.898
Outstanding!

01:28.193 --> 01:30.994
And through the generosity

01:30.996 --> 01:33.564
of Sy Goodman...

01:33.566 --> 01:37.708
the NYPD Second Tour Fund
will provide much needed support

01:37.728 --> 01:41.805
for officers forced to retire
due to line-of-duty injuries.

01:41.807 --> 01:44.841
From financial aid during recovery,

01:44.843 --> 01:48.011
to college tuition supplements
for their families,

01:48.013 --> 01:51.737
to resources required
to jump-start new careers,

01:51.757 --> 01:56.086
the fund provides a safety net
for our bravest comrades

01:56.088 --> 01:58.488
that's as overdue

01:58.490 --> 02:00.857
as it is welcome.

02:02.652 --> 02:05.996
From all of us at the NYPD, thank you.

02:07.599 --> 02:09.265
(Goodman speaks indistinctly)

02:11.469 --> 02:12.569
Goodman: You got it?

02:12.571 --> 02:14.037
You good?

02:14.039 --> 02:16.345
Frank, I got to tell you,
I'm moved, I'm deeply moved.

02:16.365 --> 02:18.442
As are we, Sy, as are we.

02:18.444 --> 02:19.943
Honor and a privilege.

02:24.315 --> 02:26.016
(sighs)

02:28.754 --> 02:30.921
If... if I may?

02:30.923 --> 02:34.291
I was just telling
our PC that I'm moved.

02:34.293 --> 02:36.671
I am deeply moved. I'm proud

02:36.691 --> 02:39.630
and... uh, filled with gratitude

02:39.632 --> 02:42.199
that I'm able to contribute,

02:42.201 --> 02:43.834
and just to play a small part

02:43.836 --> 02:46.770
in this outstanding police department.

02:46.772 --> 02:48.739
You know what,
more than that, just to...

02:48.741 --> 02:51.508
just to be able to be
on the same stage with this guy.

02:51.510 --> 02:54.544
This guy right here, salt of the earth,

02:54.546 --> 02:55.946
leader of men.

02:55.948 --> 02:58.215
You know,
when they paint his portrait...

02:58.217 --> 03:01.711
they have to put him on top
of a white horse, this guy.

03:01.731 --> 03:03.948
That's who this guy is. I...

03:03.968 --> 03:08.091
bow to no man... in my admiration...

03:08.817 --> 03:11.895
for our police commissioner,
Frank Reagan.

03:15.133 --> 03:16.733
He's got... Oh.

03:16.735 --> 03:19.147
Garrett: Thanks for
being here, everybody.

03:19.167 --> 03:21.334
That's it for today.

03:22.536 --> 03:25.571
♪ ♪

03:25.573 --> 03:27.173
Detectives. What have we go?

03:27.175 --> 03:28.608
Emily Harrison, mid-20's.

03:28.610 --> 03:30.176
Said her boyfriend held her hostage here

03:30.178 --> 03:31.844
- for 12 hours.
- Any witnesses?

03:31.846 --> 03:34.413
Roommate came home after spending
the night at her boyfriend's place

03:34.415 --> 03:37.515
but didn't see anything...
Guy'd already taken off.

03:37.890 --> 03:39.418
All right, thanks.

03:41.255 --> 03:43.956
Ms. Harrison. Detective Reagan.

03:43.958 --> 03:45.224
This is my partner, Detective Baez.

03:45.226 --> 03:46.292
How you feeling?

03:46.294 --> 03:47.526
Not great.

03:47.528 --> 03:49.295
Can you tell us what happened?

03:49.297 --> 03:51.831
I thought he was gonna kill me.

03:51.833 --> 03:53.099
Your boyfriend?

03:53.101 --> 03:56.869
(crying): Yeah, he...
he accused me of cheating.

03:56.871 --> 03:58.637
Which is crazy.

03:58.972 --> 04:01.693
When I asked him to leave,
he hit me, and then he...

04:01.713 --> 04:03.887
he handcuffed me to the bed.

04:03.907 --> 04:05.845
Did he sexually assault you, Emily?

04:05.847 --> 04:08.781
(Emily crying, sniffling)

04:08.783 --> 04:10.916
Emily: I begged him to stop.

04:10.918 --> 04:13.986
(Emily shudders, sighs)

04:13.988 --> 04:16.422
I said no.

04:16.423 --> 04:18.524
I said no over...

04:18.526 --> 04:21.961
and over and over.

04:23.318 --> 04:25.665
Can you tell us his name?

04:25.667 --> 04:27.199
Brandon Mitchell.

04:27.201 --> 04:29.935
- Any idea where we could find him?
- Yeah, he hangs out at the...

04:29.937 --> 04:31.437
at the Bengal Lounge,

04:31.439 --> 04:33.439
just a few blocks from here.

04:33.441 --> 04:35.541
He practically lives there.

04:36.435 --> 04:37.610
(whispers): Okay.

04:38.451 --> 04:40.389
Let's get her to the
hospital, all right?

04:43.415 --> 04:45.852
(quietly): Get a rape kit going, ASAP.

04:46.266 --> 04:47.853
What do you think?

04:47.855 --> 04:49.255
(sighs)

04:49.257 --> 04:51.824
Let's go get this son of a bitch.

